cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CV

The paper presents an algorithm for learning controllers for robotics systems using model-based reinforcement learning with neural networks. This falls under the intersection of several CS sub-categories, including machine learning (cs.LG), robotics (cs.RO), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), systems and control (cs.SY), and computer vision (cs.CV). Given the focus on neural networks and learning, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category. However, the application to robotics and control suggests cs.RO and cs.SY as likely sub-categories as well. The use of probabilistic models and uncertainty estimation also aligns with cs.AI. Finally, the potential application to computer vision tasks, such as object tracking, could justify cs.CV as a possible sub-category.
